=TITLE CHANGES 

=head1 Upcoming

=head1 0.0.60


=head2 @podlite/editor-react

=item fix task-list checkboxes invisible in full-preview mode — the C<content-visibility: auto> rule added in 0.0.44 was scoped to all C<.line-src> descendants, which re-introduced C<contain: size layout paint> on inner wrappers inside C<< <li> >> and broke the flex layout of C<.task-list-item>. Scoped the rule to direct children of C<.content> only; nested wrappers inside ul/ol/li/details/summary keep C<contain: none> from the existing carve-out, and the off-screen defer stays effective on top-level blocks

=head2 @podlite/schema

=item recognise the C<header> MIME parameter (RFC 4180 §3) on C<:mime-type> for CSV/TSV C<=data> blocks. When the C<=data> block declares C<:mime-type<'text/csv; header=present'>> (or the same with C<text/tab-separated-values>), C<=table data:X> marks the first row as C<:header>, which renders as C<<th>>/C<<thead>> in HTML and JSX. Default C<absent> preserves the previous behaviour. The MIME-type parser also accepts other parameters (e.g. C<charset>) without disturbing type matching. Spec: podlite-specs#25

=head2 @podlite/to-jsx

=item C<:folded> on C<=head> now folds correctly when the heading is nested inside a named block, C<=begin nested>, C<=defn>, etc. — not only at the top level of C<=begin pod>. Previously the synthetic C<_folded_section> wrapper was created only for direct children of C<pod>, so folded headings inside other containers silently rendered as plain headings. The grouping pass now walks the AST recursively, so the spec's hierarchical-fold semantics (C<:folded> on a heading governs the heading and all associated lower-level content) apply uniformly
=item replaced C<margin: 1em 0> shorthand on C<details.folded> and C<details.folded-section> with long-hand C<margin-top>/C<margin-bottom>. The shorthand zeroed horizontal margins explicitly and (because of higher selector specificity) overrode host stylesheets that center block elements via C<details { margin-left: auto }>, pinning folded sections to the parent's left edge instead of aligning with surrounding headings. Long-hand vertical-only margins let horizontal margins flow through the cascade

=head1 0.0.59


=head2 @podlite/editor-react

=item fix Enter in C<=item> list and Tab/Shift-Tab level change now scroll the cursor into view — previously the caret could move past the viewport bottom without scrolling. Same fix applied to image paste/drop insertion
=item add C<includeReader> and C<includeBaseDir> props — forwarded to the default preview C<<Podlite>> renderer so C<=include file:X> resolves at preview time. Hosts that supply a custom C<makePreviewComponent> are responsible for forwarding these themselves. Without C<includeReader> the directive renders as nothing (preserves the prior behaviour). Type C<IncludeReader> is re-exported for type-safe usage
=item add C<expandPaths> prop — forwarded to the default preview C<<Podlite>> renderer for glob-pattern resolution in C<=include file:**/*.podlite>. Type C<ExpandPaths> is re-exported

=head2 @podlite/publisher

=item extend Selector parsing: C<file:> scheme with suffix-match against C<publishRecord.file>, and pipe-separated block-name filters (e.g. C<file:terms.podlite | defn, para>). C<include-resolve-plugin> now inlines every matched block at the C<=include> location, not just the first
=item add glob support in C<file:> selectors: C<**> (any depth), C<*> (within segment), C<?> (single char). Enables patterns like C<=include file:00-DayByDay/**/term-*.podlite | defn> for full auto-aggregation across a directory tree
=item move C<parseSelector> and C<runSelector> implementation to C<@podlite/schema>. These names are still re-exported from this package, so downstream consumers that import them from C<@podlite/publisher> keep working without changes. The move breaks a circular-dependency risk for renderer-side packages that need selector mechanics (e.g. live-preview C<=include> resolution)

=head2 @podlite/schema

=item resolve C<=table data:<key>> as CSV from a C<=data :mime-type<text/csv>> block (spec §1672) — table content is replaced with C<=row>/C<=cell> structure parsed per RFC 4180 (comma delimiter, C<"...">  quoted fields with C<""> escape). Spec §1672 does not define how to mark a header in CSV-sourced tables; authors who need a header row should use a structured table with C<=begin row :header> or a Markdown GFM table. C<file:<path>> scheme is left unresolved for host-driven readers
=item resolve C<=table data:<key>> as TSV when the C<=data> block carries C<:mime-type<text/tab-separated-values>> — split on tabs only, no quoting (C<"> is a literal character, unlike CSV)
=item add table error recovery — pad short rows with empty cells, truncate over-long rows; expected cell count is taken from a C<:header> row when present, otherwise from the row with the maximum cell count. Warn on each adjustment. Tables containing C<:colspan>/C<:rowspan> cells are skipped (naive count would mis-handle spanning)
=item warn on mixed column separator types within a single text-mode C<=table> (e.g. C<|> in one row, whitespace in another) — does not block parsing
=item improve CSV/TSV error recovery — missing C<=data> block leaves the table empty; a non-tabular mime-type is rendered as a C<=code> block so the underlying content remains visible
=item add per-line separator detection for text-mode C<=table> when lines disagree about separator type. A common pattern — header with C<|> for visual emphasis and data rows aligned by whitespace alone — used to collapse columns under the unified positional mask; each line is now parsed on its own and produces the expected cells. Tables with a single separator type, or with both visible kinds (C<|>+C<+>) handled by the shared mask, still go through the legacy positional path so continuation lines in multi-line rows keep their column alignment
=item move C<parseSelector> and C<runSelector> here from C<@podlite/publisher>. These are pure AST queries (no I/O, no filesystem) and belong in C<@podlite/schema>. C<runSelector> is now generic over a C<SelectorDoc> shape (C<{ file, node }>), so consumers without the publisher's richer C<publishRecord> type can use it directly. The publisher re-exports from C<@podlite/schema> for backward compatibility

=head2 @podlite/to-jsx

=item fix C<wrapElement> no longer wraps C<=row>/C<=cell> nodes — those always render as C<<tr>>/C<<td>>, and HTML disallows arbitrary elements as children of C<<table>>/C<<tbody>>/C<<tr>>. Previously consumers that wrapped every node (e.g. an editor's line tracker injecting C<<div class="line-src">>) produced invalid HTML; browsers extracted the wrappers out of the table and collapsed cells into a vertical column. The outer C<=table> block is still wrappable
=item add C<includeReader> prop on C<<Podlite>> for resolving C<=include file:X> at render time. The reader receives a path and an optional base directory; it returns the included source as a string, or C<null> to leave the directive unresolved. The renderer parses the source, applies the selector (e.g. C<| defn>), and splices resolved blocks inline. C<ctx.includeStack> guards against include cycles. Without the prop the directive renders as nothing — preserves the previous behaviour for hosts without filesystem access
=item add C<expandPaths> prop on C<<Podlite>> for resolving glob patterns in C<=include file:X> (e.g. C<file:**/*.podlite>). The callback receives the pattern and an optional base directory; it returns a concrete list of paths. The renderer reads each path via C<includeReader>, builds a corpus, and applies the selector across all matching files. Without the prop, glob characters are read as literal path segments and resolve to nothing

=head1 0.0.58


=head2 @podlite/editor-react

=item add C<onSaveAsset> prop — paste/drop image handler. Clipboard paste (PNG/JPEG/GIF/WebP) and drag-drop (same plus SVG) are routed through the callback, which returns a relative path; the editor inserts C<=picture path> at the cursor. No-op when prop is absent
=item fix performance: in full-preview mode skip C<view.dispatch({scrollIntoView:true})> and C<getBoundingClientRect> calls on the hidden CodeMirror view; coalesce preview scroll tracking to one C<getScrollMap> pass per frame via C<requestAnimationFrame>; apply the recorded line in a single dispatch on mode exit
=item fix UX: entering full-preview scrolls the preview to the editor's current top visible line (was always line 1); leaving full-preview places the cursor on the last visible preview line and centers it at ~1/4 from the top of the editor
=item add CSS containment (C<contain: layout paint style>) to C<.line-src> wrappers and C<.podlite-editor-preview> to reduce per-paint cost during scroll
=item add C<content-visibility: auto> + C<contain-intrinsic-size: auto 2em> on C<.line-src> in full-preview mode (gated by C<data-full-preview="true"> attribute) so off-screen blocks skip layout/paint until near viewport

=head2 @podlite/schema

=item added C<type: "map"> on config items parsed from C<:attr{k=>v, ...}> key-value syntax — previously the hash form returned the map value without a type annotation, making it indistinguishable from other value kinds
=item added C<makeAttrs().getMapValue(name)> helper — returns the first map-typed value as a plain object, or undefined when the attribute is absent or not a map
=item added guillemet bracket support («...») for formatting codes A, V, S, Z, D, X — previously only angle brackets (<...>) worked for these codes
=item refactored grammarfc to use parametric rules — unified simple codes via C<FCodeSimple> template, D/X via C<FCodeWithArray>
=item bumped Pegmill dependency from 0.1.0 to 0.1.2
=item added C<O<>> strikethrough formatting code (renders to HTML C<<del>>, Markdown C<~~...~~>)
=item replaced legacy C<Delete<>> alias with canonical C<O<>> — Markdown C<~~text~~> now produces AST C<{name:'O'}>. Helper renamed C<mkFomattingCodeDelete> → C<mkFomattingCodeO>
=item added C<H<>> superscript (renders to HTML C<<sup>>) and C<J<>> subscript (renders to HTML C<<sub>>) formatting codes
=item added structured table format with C<=begin row> and C<=cell> blocks, including C<:header> attribute support (renders to HTML C<<thead>/<th>>, JSX, GFM pipe tables)
=item implicit cell wrapping: non-cell children inside C<=row> are automatically wrapped in C<=cell>
=item unified table AST across text-mode, structured and Markdown inputs — all produce C<{name:'row'}>/C<{name:'cell'}>. Legacy C<table_row>/C<table_cell>/C<table_head> node names removed
=item added C<:colspan(N)> and C<:rowspan(N)> attributes for C<=cell> blocks. Values of 1 treated as default (no attribute emitted). Markdown export falls back to inline HTML C<<table>> when any cell has spans (GFM pipe-tables don't support colspan/rowspan)
=item tables with a C<:header> row now emit semantic C<<thead>>/C<<tbody>> wrapping in HTML and JSX. Tables without headers keep the flat C<<tr>> layout

=head2 @podlite/to-jsx

=item C<:folded> on C<=head> blocks now folds the whole section — heading plus every following node up to the next same-or-higher-level heading. Previously this attribute was ignored on headings
=item per-item conditional fold for C<:folded-levels> — only TOC items that have nested children become collapsible; leaf items render as plain list entries with no disclosure marker. Previously the entire level was wrapped as a single group
=item bare C<:folded> on C<=toc> wraps the entire TOC in a C<<details>>; summary shows the caption or "Contents" fallback
=item C<:folded-levels{k=>v}> key-value syntax is now rendered (value C<1> folds that level, C<0> keeps it open)
=item CSS: disclosure markers for folded headings and foldable TOC items sit in a left gutter so that text at the same level starts on the same x-coordinate regardless of whether the item has a marker. Heading and inline content stay on one line with the triangle

=head2 @podlite/toc

=item added C<:folded-levels{k=>v}> key-value syntax — each level can now be marked folded (C<1>) or not (C<0>) independently, e.g. C<{2=>1, 3=>0}>. Array syntax C<[2,3]> still works as before
=item added bare C<:folded> attribute on C<=toc> — wraps the entire TOC in a collapsible C<<details>>. Accepts C<:!folded>/C<:folded(0)> for a disclosure that opens by default

=head1 0.0.57


=head2 @podlite/editor-react

=item add C<enableFolding> prop — control fold gutter visibility (default C<true>, C<false> for embedded editors)
=item fix embedded editor preview: align first element with editor, reduce list item spacing
=item fix C<WindowWrapper> overflow — add C<max-width: 100%> and restore C<margin: 2rem> on C<.window>
=item fix fold gutter width compensation when folding disabled (C<padding-left: 11px>)

=head1 0.0.56


=head2 @podlite/editor-react

=item fix performance: eliminate synchronous re-renders on keystroke (text state → ref, deferred onChange via rAF, 300ms debounced preview)
=item fix performance: cache verbatim ranges in fold service (O(N) per call → O(1) via document identity cache)
=item fix search panel closing after Enter on first result — memoize extensions and basicSetup to prevent CodeMirror reconfiguration on re-render
=item add C<enableCopyPng> prop to C<WindowWrapper> — copies content as PNG to clipboard via C<dom-to-image-more>
=item refactor C<WindowWrapper>: remove dead SVG foreignObject screenshot code, add TypeScript types
=item fix fold markers appearing inside verbatim blocks (C<=code>, C<=comment>, C<=data>, C<=input>, C<=output>)
=item fix cursor not visible on file open — add C<autoFocus> + reset C<initialStateApplied> on file change

=head1 0.0.55


=head2 @podlite/editor-react

=item add list continuation on Enter: auto-insert C<=itemN> with type prefix preserved (C<[ ]>, C<[x]>→C<[ ]>, C<#>)
=item pressing Enter on empty C<=itemN> (or prefix-only) exits the list
=item add Tab/Shift-Tab to increase/decrease C<=item> nesting level (2-space indent per level)
=item add code folding for C<=begin>/C<=end> blocks and C<=head> sections with fold gutter
=item add C<initialEditorState> and C<onEditorStateChange> props for session state persistence (cursor, scroll, folds)

=head2 @podlite/schema

=item added C<foldedLevels> field in C<Toc> type and C<mkToc> helper

=head2 @podlite/to-jsx

=item added C<:folded-levels> rendering for C<=toc> block -- folded levels wrapped in C<< <details> >> element

=head2 @podlite/toc

=item added C<:folded-levels> attribute for C<=toc> block -- controls which TOC levels are collapsed by default (array syntax)

